I feel justified in telling my favorite Passover joke, although most non-Jews won’t get it, so my apologies—but you will appreciate it:

A British Jew was being honored to be knighted by the Queen. It happened to be the first night of Passover but his family encouraged him to go and miss the Seder.  He came home breathless and said “The queen speaks Hebrew”. His family didn’t believe him; but he said, “No, listen. You know when you get knighted you have to kneel down and say a Latin phrase? Well I got all flustered and couldn’t remember it. All I could think of was a line from the Passover Seder, so I said ‘Ma nishtana ha laila ha zeh mekol halaylot’. And I swear the queen turned to her advisors and said ‘Why is this knight different from all the other knights?’”

