No, you can't click on the black squares, so you can't insert letters in the six DARKENERGY squares. You just have to visualize the letters there and recognize they extend both an Across and a Down answer. It's not a common NYT trick, but we have seen it before in a number of CWPs, generally Thursdays or Sundays. (I remembered this, so it delayed me but didn't fool me once I recognized what was happening, and I figured correctly that there was a significance to which letters went dark, and their sequence. Recognizing that helped me get unstuck on the last pair of theme answers that used the R.) 

