How long have you been solving for? Because such puzzle themes (whether or not you enjoy them) have been a staple of the NYT, particularly Thursday, for quite a long while—and were possibly more prevalent previously. I am currently 10 years back in the archives and see novel and unusual themes regularly. Barry and others can speak to how long they may go back even before that. So again, you may have your own preference or tolerance for out-of-the box themes, which I respect, and certainly can express it—but just wanted to point out that it isn’t a new development, and will probably continue (and if it doesn’t, would alternatively disappoint a large number of us who do appreciate less traditional themes.)

